Package com.minimalism.files.domain.entities

Class InputEntity

java.lang.Object
com.minimalism.files.domain.entities.InputEntity
Record Components:
String - name - a name that represents the nature of information in the input records; like 'HrData' or 'Wages' or 'Products'.
String - targetDomainClassName - The name of the class in the consumer service. The Entity class provides basic validation of the data, after it is read from the input file. Validation is limited to:
  1. Data type - input conforms to the specified data type - String, number, boolean, date, time
  2. Minimum Length - number of characters in the input (input is a String!) is greater or equal to specified minimum
  3. Maximum Length - number of characters in the input (input is a String!) is less than or equal to specified maximum
  4. Nullable - values is not null if specified as not-nullable
All Implemented Interfaces:
IValidation
public class InputEntity extends Object implements IValidation
Author:
R Jairam Iyer The Entity class represents a domain entity. It is a generic representation of the instances of the domain entity instances input in the file. It encapsulates a List of Field instance, which represent the attributes of the domain entity. The Entity class has the following attributes:
